THAT YOU FORGOT WHERE I AM
WHEN YOU WALK OUT?
YOU KNOW, WHEN I CAME IN TODAY,
THEY ALREADY HAD THE WINE OUT.

- AND I HAD A COUPLE DRINKS,
JUST A FEW.

- BECAUSE I KNOW THAT YOU GET
NERVOUS ON TALK SHOWS.

- I AM NERVOUS,
OH, MY GOD.

- ALL RIGHT, LET'S BRING
SOME MORE OUT FOR HER.

- BECAUSE IT'S--
YOU KIND OF STARTED SOMETHING.
YOU DRINK RED WINE ON ICE.

AND BARTENDERS ARE CALLING IT
THE KEATON.

AND SO WE THOUGHT WE SHOULD HAVE
YOUR OWN GLASSES.

- AND SO WE HAVE GLASSES
MADE FOR YOU CALLED--

HERE'S WHAT--
HERE'S HOW YOU DO IT, BABE.

- YOU JUST GRAB THAT ICE
IN YOUR HAND,

AND YOU JUST
THROW IT IN THERE.
YOU POUR IT IN THERE, RIGHT?

NO MORE, BECAUSE WE DON'T WANT
DIANE TO BE WEIRD.

SO NOW IT'S--
IT'S ALREADY WEIRD.
WE DON'T WANT DIANE TO BE WEIRD.
BUT CAN I HAVE ONE RIGHT NOW.

- OKAY, I'M GONNA GO--
DOWN IT?

- YEAH, DO YOU FEEL RELAXED?
- I FEEL GOOD.

AND, YOU KNOW, ELLEN,
I WANT TO SAY SOMETHING TO YOU.

I MENTIONED YOU IN MY BOOK,
YOU KNOW.

- AND I LOVE THE WAY DRESS,
BECAUSE, FOR EXAMPLE,

YOU SEE, THAT'S WHAT I
WANT TO WEAR, BUT--

- OH, THAT'S TRUE, TOO,
YOU KNOW?

BUT I OVERLOOKED THAT,
AND IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

YOU PROBABLY HAVE
INFLUENCED ME GREATLY.

I THINK YOU HAVE
SUCH GREAT STYLE.
AND--AND I LOVE IN YOUR BOOK,

YOU TALK ABOUT PEOPLE
THAT AREN'T CONFORMING

AND PEOPLE THAT DRESS
IN THEIR OWN STYLE

YOU KNOW, I--
AS EARLY AS, LIKE, AGE 15,

I ALREADY KNEW THAT I WAS
LIVING IN BLACK AND WHITE.

AND I WAS IN LOVE WITH
CARY GRANT.

AND, IN FACT, I NAMED
MY DAUGHTER C.K. DEXTER HAVEN

AFTER CARY GRANT IN
"THE PHILADELPHIA STORY."

AND I JUST LOVE
"THE PHILADELPHIA STORY."
HE WAS--I DON'T KNOW IF YOU GUYS

ARE AT ALL FAMILIAR
WITH CARY GRANT.

AND HE HAD THOSE
HORNED-RIMMED GLASSES,

AND HE WAS JUST
THE EPITOME OF STYLE,

HE WAS THE ONE WHO SAID
"CLOTHES MAKE THE MAN."

HE WAS THE FIRST ONE.
- OH, REALLY?

- YEAH, AND HE ALSO SAID
THAT HE ALWAYS--

HE PRETENDED THAT HE WAS
SOMEBODY THAT HE WANTED TO BE,

AN FINALLY HE BECAME
THAT PERSON,

WHICH I JUST LOVE
THE CONCEPT OF THAT,

BECAUSE IT MEANS
WE'RE THE OWNER OF OUR LIVES,
THAT WE CAN DO ANYTHING WE WANT

IF WE REALLY
PUT IT TO OURSELVES.

YOU HAVE A BEAUTIFUL AUDIENCE
TODAY, TOO.
DO YOU MIND IF I HAVE ANOTHER?
- I'M GETTING USED TO THIS NOW.
- NOW, WILL YOU BE DOING THIS?

YOU KNOW, WE'RE FINALLY--
AFTER TEN YEARS,

THEY'RE MAKING A SEQUEL
TO "FINDING NEMO,"

AND IT'S "FINDING DORY,"
WHICH IS MY FISH.

AND DIANE IS PLAYING MY MOTHER
IN THE FILM.
WE BOTH HAVE THE SAME PROBLEM.

IN THE FILM, FOR--
IN THE FILM.

BUT I ALSO--
IN REAL LIFE I HAVE THAT.
- THAT'S WHAT I JUST ASKED YOU.

DO YOU REMEMBER ME
ASKING YOU THAT?
I JUST SAID IT A SECOND AGO.
- YOU SAID THE THING OF WHAT?
AND THEN WHAT DID YOU SAY?
IT WAS WAITING FOR AN ANSWER?

- IT WAS JUST THAT QUESTION.
- NO, YEAH, THAT'S THE QUESTION.

- AND THAT WAS REALLY
SO AMAZING,

AND YOU JUST KIND OF DISCOVER
THE PROCESS IN THE PROCESS.

- AND THEN I SAID--
I ASKED THEM,

WAS THERE A CHANCE THAT I'D BE
WORKING WITH YOU.

AS THE PEOPLE
WHO DON'T HAVE THE MEMORY?

- YES, AND YOU'RE A FISH.
THE WHOLE--
- HAVE YOU SEEN THE FIRST ONE?
